# Arrays vs. Linked Lists

## 1. Memory Allocation
- **Arrays:** Contiguous memory allocation (fixed size).
- **Linked Lists:** Dynamic memory allocation (nodes stored anywhere).

## 2. Performance
| Feature | Arrays | Linked Lists |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| Access Time | O(1) (Direct index access) | O(n) (Sequential traversal) |
| Search Time | O(n) (Unsorted), O(log n) (Sorted) | O(n) |

## 3. Insertion & Deletion
- **Arrays:** Costly insert/delete (shifting elements).
- **Linked Lists:** Faster insert/delete (pointer manipulation).
